context: Raleigh is also served by Triangle Transit (known formerly as the <a0_0><b5_0>Triangle Transit Authority<b5_0/>,<a0_0/> or TTA). <b8_0>Triangle Transit<b8_0/> offers <a1_0><b6_0>scheduled, fixed-route regional and <b7_0>commuter bus service<b7_0/><b6_0/><a1_0/> between Raleigh and the region's other principal cities of Durham, Cary and Chapel Hill, as well as to and from the <a2_0>Raleigh-Durham International Airport, Research Triangle Park<a2_0/> and several of the region's larger suburban communities. <a3_0>Triangle Transit also coordinates an extensive vanpool<a3_0/> and <a4_0>rideshare program that serves the region's larger employers<a4_0/> and commute destinations.
